          <source>Storage accounts let you create a group of data management rules and apply them all at once to the data stored in the account: blobs, files, tables, and queues.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If you tried to achieve the same thing without storage accounts, the end product would be tedious and error-prone.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, what are the chances that you could successfully apply the same rules to thousands of blobs?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Instead, you capture the rules in the settings for a storage account, and those rules are automatically applied to every data service in the account.</source>
        </trans-unit></group></body></file></xliff>